Q.Given a string, reverse all the words which have odd length. The even length words are not changed.


func reverseOdd (sentence str : String) -> String{
    var arr = str.split(separator: " ")
    var ans = ""
    for sub in arr{
        if sub.count % 2 != 0{
            ans += sub.reversed()+" "
        }
        else{
            ans += sub+" "
        }
    }
    return ans
}
    print(reverseOdd(sentence: "When you define a function, you can optionally define one or more named, typed values that the function takes as input, known as parameters"))





Output:

When uoy define a ,noitcnuf uoy nac optionally define eno or more named, depyt values that eht function sekat as input, nwonk as parameters 
